Firefighters attempt to extinguish a fire burning in the National Assembly, the main chamber of the South African Parliament buildings in Cape Town. Rodger Bosch/ AFP CAPE TOWN - The National Assembly's sprinkler valves have not been serviced since 2021. This is according to a report by the City of Cape Town Fire's report released on Friday. READ: Parliament considering alternative venues for SONA, budget According to the report, fire doors were latched from the outside and could not prevent the spread of the fire. The sprinklers did not activate in the Old Assembly Building and the emergency staircases were poorly ventilated. Fire Safety Observations Parliamentary Complex 2 January 2022 (1) by eNCA.com on Scribd 